168inline constexpr MachineType CommonMachineType(MachineType type1,
169 MachineType type2) {
170 return (type1 == type2) ? type1
171 : ((type1.IsTagged() && type2.IsTagged())
172 ? MachineType::AnyTagged()
173 : MachineType::None());
174}

220template <class T1, class T2>

226template <class Type, class Enable = void>
227struct MachineRepresentationOf {
228 static const MachineRepresentation value = Type::kMachineRepresentation;
229};
230// If T defines kMachineType, then we take the machine representation from
231// there.
232template <class T>
233struct MachineRepresentationOf<T, std::void_t<decltype(T::kMachineType)>> {
234 static constexpr MachineRepresentation value =
235 T::kMachineType.representation();
236};
237template <class T>
238struct MachineRepresentationOf<T, std::enable_if_t<is_taggable_v<T>>> {
239 static constexpr MachineRepresentation value =
240 MachineTypeOf<T>::value.representation();
241};
242template <>
243struct MachineRepresentationOf<ExternalReference> {
244 static constexpr MachineRepresentation value =
245 RawPtrT::kMachineRepresentation;
246};
247
248template <typename T>
249constexpr bool IsMachineRepresentationOf(MachineRepresentation r) {
250 return MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value == r;
251}

253template <class T>
254constexpr MachineRepresentation PhiMachineRepresentationOf =
255 std::is_base_of<Word32T, T>::value ? MachineRepresentation::kWord32
256 : MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value;

258template <class T>
259struct is_valid_type_tag {
260 static const bool value = is_taggable_v<T> ||
261 std::is_base_of<UntaggedT, T>::value ||
262 std::is_same<ExternalReference, T>::value;
263 static const bool is_tagged = is_taggable_v<T>;
264};
265
266template <class T1, class T2>
267struct is_valid_type_tag<PairT<T1, T2>> {
268 static const bool value =
269 is_valid_type_tag<T1>::value && is_valid_type_tag<T2>::value;
270 static const bool is_tagged = false;
271};
272
273template <class T1, class T2>
274struct is_valid_type_tag<UnionT<T1, T2>> {
275 static const bool is_tagged =
276 is_valid_type_tag<T1>::is_tagged && is_valid_type_tag<T2>::is_tagged;
277 static const bool value = is_tagged;
278};
279
280template <class T1, class T2>
281struct UnionT {
282 static_assert(CommonMachineType(MachineTypeOf<T1>::value,
283 MachineTypeOf<T2>::value)
284 .representation() != MachineRepresentation::kNone,
285 "no common representation");
286 static_assert(is_valid_type_tag<T1>::is_tagged &&
287 is_valid_type_tag<T2>::is_tagged,
288 "union types are only possible for tagged values");
289};

293using Numeric = UnionT<Number, BigInt>;
294using ContextOrEmptyContext = UnionT<Context, Smi>;

299template <class T1, class T2, class U>
300struct is_subtype<UnionT<T1, T2>, U, 1>
301 : public std::conjunction<is_subtype<T1, U>, is_subtype<T2, U>> {};
302template <class T, class U1, class U2>
303struct is_subtype<T, UnionT<U1, U2>, 1>
304 : public std::disjunction<is_subtype<T, U1>, is_subtype<T, U2>> {};
305template <class T1, class T2, class U1, class U2>
306struct is_subtype<UnionT<T1, T2>, UnionT<U1, U2>, 1>
307 : public std::conjunction<is_subtype<T1, UnionT<U1, U2>>,
308 is_subtype<T2, UnionT<U1, U2>>> {};
309template <>
310struct is_subtype<ExternalReference, RawPtrT> {
311 static const bool value = true;
312};

325};

327struct types_have_common_values<Int32T, U> {
328 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<Word32T, U>::value;
329};

331struct types_have_common_values<Uint64T, U> {
332 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<Word64T, U>::value;
333};
334template <class U>
335struct types_have_common_values<Int64T, U> {
336 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<Word64T, U>::value;
337};
338template <class U>
339struct types_have_common_values<IntPtrT, U> {
340 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<WordT, U>::value;
341};
342template <class U>
343struct types_have_common_values<UintPtrT, U> {
344 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<WordT, U>::value;
345};
346template <class T1, class T2, class U>
347struct types_have_common_values<UnionT<T1, T2>, U> {
348 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<T1, U>::value ||
349 types_have_common_values<T2, U>::value;
350};

352template <class T, class U1, class U2>
353struct types_have_common_values<T, UnionT<U1, U2>> {
354 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<T, U1>::value ||
355 types_have_common_values<T, U2>::value;
356};
357template <class T1, class T2, class U1, class U2>
358struct types_have_common_values<UnionT<T1, T2>, UnionT<U1, U2>> {
359 static const bool value = types_have_common_values<T1, U1>::value ||
360 types_have_common_values<T1, U2>::value ||
361 types_have_common_values<T2, U1>::value ||
362 types_have_common_values<T2, U2>::value;
363};

365// TNode<T> is an SSA value with the static type tag T, which is one of the
366// following:
367// - MaybeObject> represents the type of all tagged values, including weak
368// pointers.
369// - a subclass of internal::Object represents a non-weak tagged type.
370// - a subclass of internal::UntaggedT represents an untagged type
371// - ExternalReference
372// - PairT<T1, T2> for an operation returning two values, with types T1
373// and T2
374// - UnionT<T1, T2> represents either a value of type T1 or of type T2.
375template <class T>
376class TNode {
377 public:
378 template <class U, typename = std::enable_if_t<is_subtype<U, T>::value>>
379 TNode(const TNode<U>& other) V8_NOEXCEPT : node_(other.node_) {
380 LazyTemplateChecks();
381 }
382
383 TNode(const TNode& other) V8_NOEXCEPT : node_(other.node_) {}
384 TNode() : node_(nullptr) {}
385
386 TNode operator=(TNode other) {
387 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(other.node_);
388 node_ = other.node_;
389 return *this;
390 }
391
392 operator compiler::Node*() const { return node_; }
393
394 explicit operator bool() const { return node_ != nullptr; }
395
396 static TNode UncheckedCast(compiler::Node* node) { return TNode(node); }
397
398 protected:
399 template <typename U>
400 friend class TNode;
401
402 explicit TNode(compiler::Node* node) : node_(node) { LazyTemplateChecks(); }
403 // These checks shouldn't be checked before TNode is actually used.
404 void LazyTemplateChecks() const {
405 static_assert(is_valid_type_tag<T>::value, "invalid type tag");
406 }
407
408 compiler::Node* node_;
409};
410
411template <class T>
412class TNode<Tagged<T>> {
413 static_assert(!std::is_same_v<T, T>,
414 "Don't write TNode<Tagged<T>>, just write TNode<T> directly.");
415};
416
417// SloppyTNode<T> is a variant of TNode<T> and allows implicit casts from
418// Node*. It is intended for function arguments as long as some call sites
419// still use untyped Node* arguments.
420// TODO(turbofan): Delete this class once transition is finished.
421template <class T>
422class SloppyTNode : public TNode<T> {
423 public:
424 SloppyTNode(compiler::Node* node) // NOLINT(runtime/explicit)
425 : TNode<T>(node) {}
426 template <class U, typename std::enable_if<is_subtype<U, T>::value,
427 int>::type = 0>
428 SloppyTNode(const TNode<U>& other) V8_NOEXCEPT // NOLINT(runtime/explicit)
429 : TNode<T>(other) {}
430};
